---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - TimeHopper">
    <div class="legal-container">
        <div class="header">
            <a href="/index.html" class="logo">
                <img src="/images/icon48.png" alt="TimeHopper Logo" style="width: 32px; height: 32px;">
                TimeHopper
            </a>
        </div>

        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: January 29, 2026</p>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper ("we", "our", or "us") is a Chrome Extension designed to help you manage time zones and schedule
                meetings. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper accesses the minimum amount of data necessary to function:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Calendar Data:</strong> We access your Google Calendar events strictly to display them to you in
                    the extension popup and to provide meeting notifications. This data is fetched directly from Google's
                    APIs and is stored locally in your browser. We do not transmit this data to any external servers.</li>
                <li><strong>User Preferences:</strong> using Chrome Storage, we save your settings (such as selected time
                    zones, working hours, and notification preferences).</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We use aggregated, anonymous analytics (via <strong>Amplitude</strong>) to understand feature
                    usage and improve the product. This data does not contain personally identifiable information (PII) or
                    calendar details. No calendar content is ever sent to analytics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Security and Protection Mechanisms</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper employs multiple technical layers of security to safeguard your sensitive Google user data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Encryption in Transit:</strong> All communications between the TimeHopper extension and Google APIs are secured using <strong>HTTPS (TLS 1.2+)</strong> encryption. This ensures that your calendar information cannot be intercepted by third parties during transmission.</li>
                <li><strong>Sandboxed Local Storage:</strong> TimeHopper does not transmit or store your calendar data on external servers. All data is saved exclusively within the browser's <strong>protected local storage</strong>, which is isolated from other websites and extensions through browser-level sandboxing.</li>
                <li><strong>Secure Token Management:</strong> OAuth 2.0 credentials and access tokens are handled using strict security procedures. They are stored securely within the browser and are never transmitted in plaintext. All tokens are revoked and permanently deleted when you sign out or uninstall the extension.</li>
                <li><strong>No AI Training:</strong> We guarantee that no information from your Google Calendar is used to train Large Language Models (LLMs) or any other machine learning systems.</li>
                <li><strong>Limited Use Compliance:</strong> TimeHopper's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs to any other app will adhere to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To display your upcoming schedule and time blocks.</li>
                <li>To provide desktop notifications for upcoming meetings.</li>
                <li>To calculate time zone overlaps for team coordination.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties. As noted above, we use Amplitude for anonymous product analytics, and Google APIs for fetching your calendar data directly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a
                    href="mailto:support@timehopper.app">support@timehopper.app</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    .legal-container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 20px;
    }

    .header {
        padding-bottom: 30px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .logo {
        font-size: 24px;
        font-weight: 800;
        color: #333;
        text-decoration: none;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5em;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        color: #2c3e50;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .section {
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
</style>
